0044074\nname: obsolete negative regulation by symbiont of host translation\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. The process in which a symbiont organism stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of translation, the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of a protein, in its host organism.\" [MITRE:tk]\ncomment: This term was obsoleted because it represents the same process as symbiont-mediated suppression of host translation ; GO:0039604.\nsynonym: \"negative regulation of host translation by symbiont\" EXACT []\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26747\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\nreplaced_by: GO:0039604\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0044075\nname: symbiont-mediated perturbation of host vacuole organization\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which a symbiont alters or subverts vacuole organization in its host organism. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [PMID:25139904]\nsynonym: \"modulation by symbiont of host vacuole biogenesis\" RELATED [GOC:mah]\nsynonym: \"modulation by symbiont of host vacuole organisation\" EXACT [GOC:mah]\nsynonym: \"modulation by symbiont of host vacuole organization\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"modulation of host vacuole organization by symbiont\" EXACT [GOC:mah]\nsynonym: \"regulation by symbiont of host vacuole organization\" EXACT [GOC:mah]\nintersection_of: GO:0044003 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host process\nintersection_of: regulates_in_another_organism GO:0007033 ! vacuole organization\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26251\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0044077\nname: symbiont-mediated perturbation of host receptor-mediated endocytosis\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which a symbiont initiates, promotes, or enhances host receptor-mediated endocytosis, the uptake of external materials by cells,