naling\" EXACT []\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/25395\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/25988\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0044082\nname: symbiont-mediated perturbation of host small GTPase-mediated signal transduction\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which a symbiont alters or subverts a small GTPase-mediated signal transduction pathway in its host organism. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [MITRE:tk]\nsynonym: \"modulation by symbiont of host small GTPase mediated signal transduction\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"modulation of host small GTPase mediated signal transduction by symbiont\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"perturbation of host small GTPase mediated signal transduction\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"regulation by symbiont of host small GTPase mediated signal transduction\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0051056 ! regulation of small GTPase mediated signal transduction\nis_a: GO:0052027 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host signal transduction pathway\nintersection_of: GO:0044003 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host process\nintersection_of: regulates_in_another_organism GO:0007264 ! small GTPase-mediated signal transduction\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/25571\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0044083\nname: symbiont-mediated perturbation of host Rho small GTPase signal transduction\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which a symbiont alters a Rho protein family-mediated signal transduction pathway in its host organism. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [PMID:15694861, PMID:17689917, PMID:30201700]\nsynonym: \"modulation by symbiont of host Rho protein mediated signal transduction\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"modulation by symbiont of host Rho protein signal transduction\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"modulation by symbiont of host Rho protein-mediated signal transduction\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"modulation of host Rho protein signal transduction by symbiont\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"modulation of host Rho protein signaling by symbiont\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"modulation of host Rho protein signalling by symbiont\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"perturbation of host Rho protein signal transduction\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"regulation by symbiont of host Rho protein signal transduction\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"symbiont-mediated perturbation of host Rho protein signal transduction\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0044082 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host small GTPase-mediated signal transduction\nintersection_of: GO:0044003 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host process\nintersection_of: regulates_in_another_organism GO:0007266 ! Rho protein signal transduction\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28235\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0044414\nname: symbiont-mediated suppression of host defenses\nnamespace: biological_process\nalt_id: GO:0051833\nalt_id: GO:0052037\nalt_id: GO:0052261\ndef: \"A process in which a symbiont interferes with, inhibits or disrupts the normal execution of host defense(s) by active mechanisms that normally result in the shutting down of a host pathway. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [GOC:curators]\nsynonym: \"down regulation by organism of defense response of other organism during symbiotic interaction\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"down regulation by symbiont of host defense response\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"down-regulation by organism of defense response of other organism during symbiotic interaction\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"down-regulation by symbiont of host defense response\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"downregulation by organism of defense response of other organism during symbiotic interaction\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"downregulation by symbiont of host defense response\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"inhibition by organism of defense response of other organism during symbiotic interaction\" NARROW []\nsynonym: \"inhibition by symbiont of host defense response\" NARROW []\nsynonym: \"negative regulation by organism of defense response of other organism during symbiotic interaction\" RELATED [GOC:dph]\nsynonym: \"negative regulation by organism of defense response of other organism involved in symbiotic interaction\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"negative regulation by symbiont of host defense response\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"negative regulation of host defenses\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"suppression of defense response of other organism\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"suppression of defense response of other organism involved in symbiotic interaction\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"suppression of defenses of other organism involved in symbiotic interaction\" BROAD []\nsynonym: \"suppression of host defense response\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"suppression of host defenses by symbiont\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0030682 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host defenses\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/24970\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0044542\nname: symbiont-mediated activation of host plasminogen\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which a symbiont initiates, promotes, or enhances the normal activation of plasminogen, the pathway resulting in the processing of inactive plasminogen to active plasmin in the host organism. This can facilitate the dissemination of the symbiont into host tissues. It can also be used to destroy complement, opsonins as well as antibacterial proteins like histones.\" [PMID:18070889, PMID:27533300, PMID:34305859]\nsynonym: \"plasminogen activation in another organism\" BROAD []\nsynonym: \"plasminogen activation in other organism\" BROAD []\nintersection_of: GO:0044003 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host process\nintersection_of: positively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0031639 ! plasminogen activation\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26812\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: jl\ncreation_date: 2012-03-22T11:40:03Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0044552\nname: obsolete symbiont-mediated vasodilation in host\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. A process in which a symbiont causes vasodilation of blood vessels in its host organism, usually causing a reduction in blood pressure. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [GOC:ecd, GOC:jl, PMID:15637157]\ncomment: This term was obsoleted because it is too general.\nsynonym: \"modulation of vasodilation in other organism\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"regulation of vasodilation in other organism\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"vasodilation in other organism\" EXACT []\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29564\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\ncreated_by: jl\ncreation_date: 2012-03-29T02:14:42Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0044645\nname: obsolete modulation of complement activation in another organism\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. A process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of complement activation in a different organism.\" [GOC:fj, GOC:jl, PMID:20837040]\ncomment: This term was obsoleted because it is too general ; consider symbiont-mediated suppression of host complement activation ; GO:0042784.\nsynonym: \"modulation of complement activation in other organism\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"regulation of complement activation in other organism\" EXACT []\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26389\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\nconsider: GO:0042784\ncreated_by: jl\ncreation_date: 2012-07-11T12:37:50Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0044658\nname: symbiont-mediated pore formation in host plasma membrane\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The disruption of host plasma membrane integrity by formation of a pore, resulting in deregulated ion homeostasis, and cellular dysfunction that can result in cell death.\" [GOC:jl, PMID:7510043]\nsynonym: \"pore formation in host plasma membrane\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"pore formation in membrane of host by symbiont\" BROAD []\nis_a: GO:0141171 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host membrane\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/24127\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/25236\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: jl\ncreation_date: 2012-08-01T13:14:42Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0044659\nname: viral release from host cell by cytolysis\nnamespace: biological_process\nalt_id: GO:0019077\nalt_id: GO:0046756\ndef: \"The dissemination of mature viral particles from a host cell by the rupture of cell membranes and the loss of cytoplasm.\" [GOC:jl, PMID:26728778]\nsynonym: \"cytolysis by virus of host cell\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"lytic viral life cycle\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"lytic viral release\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"viral exit from host cell by cytolysis\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"viral release by cell lysis\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"viral release by host cell lysis\" EXACT []\nxref: VZ:1077 \"Cell lysis\"\nis_a: GO:0001897 ! symbiont-mediated cytolysis of host cell\nis_a: GO:0016032 ! viral process\nis_a: GO:0019076 ! viral release from host cell\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/18852\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: jl\ncreation_date: 2012-08-01T13:16:39Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0044660\nname: viral release via pore formation in host cell membrane\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The dissemination of mature viral particles from a host cell via the formation by the virus of pores in its host cell membrane.\" [GOC:jl]\nsynonym: \"cytolysis by virus via pore formation in host cell membrane\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"viral exit by cytolysis via pore formation in host cell membrane\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"viral release by cytolysis via pore formation in host cell membrane\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0044659 ! viral release from host cell by cytolysis\nrelationship: has_part GO:0044658 ! symbiont-mediated pore formation in host plasma membrane\nrelationship: has_part GO:0051673 ! disruption of plasma membrane integrity in another organism\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/18852\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/24035\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/24077\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: jl\ncreation_date: 2012-08-01T13:23:41Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0044694\nname: symbiont genome entry into host cell via pore formation in plasma membrane\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"Entry of a symbiont's genome into a host cell by a pore formed by the symbiont in the host cell. Examples of this process include injection by a non-enveloped virus of the viral genome into the host cytoplasm, usually mediated by a viral pore-forming peptide associated with the viral capsid or bacteriophage tail.\" [GOC:jl, VZ:979]\ncomment: This mechanism is used by animal viruses such as poliovirus. Various tailed bacteriophages also carry specialized proteins which open a pore or a channel in the host membrane(s) to allow genome delivery into host cytoplasm.\nsynonym: \"membrane puncture-mediated penetration of viral genome into host cell\" RELATED [UniProtKB-KW:KW-1172]\nsynonym: \"pore-mediated entry of viral genome into host cell\" NARROW []\nsynonym: \"pore-mediated penetration of viral genome into host cell\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"viral entry via genome injection\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"viral genome delivery via icosahedral vertex\" NARROW []\nsynonym: \"viral genome translocation\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"viral pore-forming protein\" NARROW [GOC:bf]\nxref: VZ:979 \"Pore-mediated penetration of viral genome into host cell\"\nis_a: GO:0141171 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host membrane\nrelationship: part_of GO:0046718 ! symbiont entry into host cell\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26670\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: jl\ncreation_date: 2012-08-16T11:08:02Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0044696\nname: killing by virus of host cell by post-segregational killing\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The process by which a virus causes the death of daughter cells which do not contain its genes after host cell division, by a mechanism of post-segregational killing (PSK). The extrachromosomal viral DNA consist of two genes; the product of the second is long lived and toxic, while the product of the first is short lived and antagonizes the lethal action of the toxin. Daughter cells that do not contain the viral extrachromosomal element are killed by the long lived toxin, while daughter cells that do contain the viral extrachromosomal element are protected by the action of the short lived antitoxin it encodes.\" [GOC:bf, GOC:jl, PMID:11222604, Wikipedia:Toxin-antitoxin_system]\ncomment: Note that this process occurs after the cell division partitioning event.\nsynonym: \"killing by virus of host cell by PSK\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"killing by virus of host cell by toxin-antitoxin system\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0001907 ! symbiont-mediated killing of host cell\ncreated_by: jl\ncreation_date: 2012-08-16T13:58:18Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0044758\nname: symbiont-mediated perturbation of host synaptic transmission\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which a symbiont alters or subverts synaptic transmission, the communication from a neuron to a target (neuron, muscle, or secretory cell) across a synapse, in its host organism.\" [GOC:jl, PMID:26487282, PMID:31075318]\nsynonym: \"modulation by symbiont of host synaptic transmission\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"regulation by symbiont of host synaptic transmission\" EXACT []\nintersection_of: GO:0044003 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host process\nintersection_of: regulates_in_another_organism GO:0007268 ! chemical synaptic transmission\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28791\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: jl\ncreation_date: 2012-12-06T15:34:05Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0044759\nname: symbiont-mediated suppression of host synaptic transmission\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which a symbiont inhibits or disrupts the normal execution of synaptic transmission, communication from a neuron to a target (neuron, muscle, or secretory cell) across a synapse, in its host organism.\" [GOC:jl]\nsynonym: \"negative regulation by symbiont of host synaptic transmission\" EXACT []\nintersection_of: GO:0044003 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host process\nintersection_of: negatively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0007268 ! chemical synaptic transmission\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28791\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: jl\ncreation_date: 2012-12-06T15:37:25Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0044760\nname: symbiont-mediated perturbation of host cholinergic synaptic transmission\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which a symbiont alters or subverts cholinergic synaptic transmission, the communication from a neuron to a target (neuron, muscle, or secretory cell) across a synapse via the neurotransmitter choline, in its host organism.\" [GOC:jl]\nsynonym: \"modulation by symbiont of host cholinergic synaptic transmission\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"regulation by symbiont of host cholinergic synaptic transmission\" EXACT []\nintersection_of: GO:0044003 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host process\nintersection_of: regulates_in_another_organism GO:0007271 ! synaptic transmission, cholinergic\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28791\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: jl\ncreation_date: 2012-12-06T15:39:46Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0044761\nname: symbiont-mediated suppression of host cholinergic synaptic transmission\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which a symbiont inhibits or disrupts the normal execution of cholinergic synaptic transmission, communication from a neuron to a target (neuron, muscle, or secretory cell) across a synapse via the neurotransmitter choline, in its host organism.\" [GOC:jl, PMID:37157163]\nsynonym: \"negative regulation by symbiont of host cholinergic synaptic transmission\" EXACT []\nintersection_of: GO:0044003 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host process\nintersection_of: negatively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0007271 ! synaptic transmission, cholinergic\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28791\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: jl\ncreation_date: 2012-12-06T15:43:53Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0044762\nname: symbiont-mediated suppression of host neurotransmitter secretion\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which a symbiont inhibits or disrupts the regulated release of a neurotransmitter from a cell in its host organism.\" [PMID:1328520, PMID:7901002]\nsynonym: \"negative regulation by symbiont of host neurotransmitter secretion\" EXACT []\nintersection_of: GO:0044003 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host process\nintersection_of: negatively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0007269 ! neurotransmitter secretion\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/27128\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: jl\ncreation_date: 2012-12-06T15:52:20Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0044865\nname: symbiont-mediated suppression of host cell division\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which a symbiont inhibits or disrupts the normal execution of cell division in the host cell. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [PMID:24218612]\nsynonym: \"inhibition by virus of host cell division\" NARROW []\nsynonym: \"negative regulation by virus of host cell division\" NARROW []\nintersection_of: GO:0044003 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host process\nintersection_of: negatively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0051301 ! cell division\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26621\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: jl\ncreation_date: 2014-08-05T16:31:44Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0046773\nname: symbiont-mediated suppression of host translation termination\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which a symbiont inhibits or disrupts translation termination of host mRNAs. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [ISBN:0781718325]\nsynonym: \"suppression by virus of host translation termination\" NARROW []\nsynonym: \"viral inhibition of termination of host cell protein biosynthesis\" NARROW []\nsynonym: \"viral inhibition of termination of host cell protein biosynthetic process\" NARROW []\nsynonym: \"viral suppression of termination by host of host cell protein biosynthesis\" NARROW []\nsynonym: \"viral suppression of termination by host of host cell protein biosynthetic process\" NARROW []\nis_a: GO:0039656 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host gene expression\nintersection_of: GO:0044003 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host process\nintersection_of: negatively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0006415 ! translational termination\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26747\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0046774\nname: obsolete suppression by virus of host intracellular interferon activity\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. Any viral process that results in the inhibition of interferon activity within the host cell.\" [PMID:10859382]\ncomment: This term was obsoleted because it was overlapping with symbiont-mediated suppression of host interferon-mediated signaling pathway ; GO:0140886.\nsynonym: \"negative regulation by virus of intracellular interferon activity\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"suppression by virus of intracellular interferon activity in host\" EXACT []\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29194\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\nconsider: GO:0140886\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0046776\nname: symbiont-mediated suppression of host antigen processing and presentation of peptide antigen via MHC class I\nnamespace: biological_process\nalt_id: GO:0039591\ndef: \"A process by which a symbiont inhibits or disrupts the normal processing and presentation of a peptide antigen on its cell surface in association with an MHC class I transmembrane protein complex. One mechanism of suppression is by direct inhibition of host tapasin, a type I transmembrane protein essential for the optimal expression of stable MHC class I molecules on the host cell surface. By inhibiting host tapasin activity, some viruses can prevent presentation of their antigens at the cell surface, and thereby evade the host anti-viral immune response.\" [GOC:add, GOC:bf, PMID:10227971, PMID:10859382, PMID:9175839]\nsynonym: \"inhibition of host MHC class I molecule presentation by virus\" NARROW []\nsynonym: \"negative regulation by virus of MHC class I cell surface presentation\" NARROW []\nsynonym: \"suppression by virus of host antigen processing and presentation of peptide antigen via MHC class I\" NARROW []\nsynonym: \"suppression by virus of host MHC class I cell surface presentation\" NARROW [GOC:add]\nsynonym: \"suppression by virus of host tapasin activity\" NARROW []\nsynonym: \"suppression by virus of MHC class I cell surface presentation in host\" NARROW []\nis_a: GO:0039588 ! symbiont-mediated suppression of host antigen processing and presentation\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/22150\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26738\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0046780\nname: symbiont-mediated suppression of host mRNA splicing\nnamespace: biological_process\nalt_id: GO:0046781\ndef: \"A process in which a symbiont inhibits or disrupts the splicing of host mRNA, thus interfering with normal host protein production. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [PMID:12660167, PMID:19729513]\nsynonym: \"negative regulation by virus of host mRNA splicing\" NARROW []\nsynonym: \"suppression by virus of host mRNA splicing\" NARROW []\nsynonym: \"suppression by virus of host splicing factor activity\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"viral dispersion of host splicing factors\" NARROW []\nsynonym: \"viral inhibition of host mRNA splicing\" NARROW []\nintersection_of: GO:0044003 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host process\nintersection_of: negatively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0000398 ! mRNA splicing, via spliceosome\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26747\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0046783\nname: obsolete modification by virus of host polysomes\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. Any viral process that interferes with and inhibits the assembly and function of polysomes.\" [PMID:10438802]\ncomment: This term was obsoleted because it represents the same process as symbiont-mediated inactivation of host ribosome ; GO:0141130.\nsynonym: \"viral perturbation of polysomes\" EXACT []\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26747\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\nreplaced_by: GO:0141130\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0051819\nname: symbiont-mediated induction of tumor or growth in host\nnamespace: biological_process\nalt_id: GO:0044005\nalt_id: GO:0044006\nalt_id: GO:0051820\ndef: \"The process in which a symbiont causes the formation of a mass of cells in a host organism. While these growths are often called nodules, they are not formed as n