ve response\" EXACT [GOC:pamgo_curators]\nxref: Wikipedia:Effector-triggered_immunity\nis_a: GO:0052042 ! symbiont-mediated activation of host programmed cell death\nis_a: GO:0052158 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host resistance gene-dependent defense response\nis_a: GO:0140404 ! effector-mediated perturbation of host innate immune response by symbiont\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/18694\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: dhl\ncreation_date: 2011-08-10T04:33:53Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0085032\nname: symbiont-mediated perturbation of host NF-kappaB cascade\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which a symbiont alters or subverts an NF-kappaB-mediated signaling cascade in its host organism. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [GOC:pamgo_curators]\nsynonym: \"modulation by symbiont of host I-kappaB kinase/NF-kappaB cascade\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"modulation by symbiont of host NF-kappaB-mediated signal transduction pathway\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"perturbation of host canonical NF-kappaB cascade\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"perturbation of host I-kappaB kinase/NF-kappaB cascade\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"symbiont-mediated perturbation of host canonical NF-kappaB cascade\" RELATED []\nis_a: GO:0052027 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host signal transduction pathway\nintersection_of: GO:0044003 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host process\nintersection_of: regulates_in_another_organism GO:0007249 ! canonical NF-kappaB signal transduction\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/25571\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: jl\ncreation_date: 2010-07-27T02:13:37Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0085033\nname: symbiont-mediated activation of host NF-kappaB cascade\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process that initiates, promotes, or enhances a host NF-kappaB-mediated signaling cascade. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [PMID:11907233, PMID:17490702, PMID:21098302, PMID:21199955, PMID:31311877, PMID:7845680]\nsynonym: \"activation by symbiont of host I-kappaB kinase/NF-kappaB cascade\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"induction by symbiont of host I-kappaB kinase/NF-kappaB cascade\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"induction of host canonical NF-kappaB signal transduction\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"induction of host I-kappaB kinase/NF-kappaB cascade\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"positive regulation by symbiont of host I-kappaB kinase/NF-kappaB cascade\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"positive regulation by symbiont of host NF-kappaB-mediated signal transduction pathway\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"stimulation by symbiont of host I-kappaB kinase/NF-kappaB cascade\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"symbiont-mediated activation of host canonical NF-kappaB signal transduction\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"symbiont-mediated activation of host NF-kappaB signal transduction\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"up regulation by symbiont of host I-kappaB kinase/NF-kappaB cascade\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"up-regulation by symbiont of host I-kappaB kinase/NF-kappaB cascade\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"upregulation by symbiont of host I-kappaB kinase/NF-kappaB cascade\" EXACT []\nxref: VZ:841\nis_a: GO:0085032 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host NF-kappaB cascade\nintersection_of: GO:0044003 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host process\nintersection_of: positively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0007249 ! canonical NF-kappaB signal transduction\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/25571\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26686\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: jl\ncreation_date: 2010-07-27T02:47:01Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0085034\nname: symbiont-mediated suppression of host NF-kappaB cascade\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which a symbiont interferes with, inhibits or disrupts an NF-kappaB-mediated signaling cascade in its host organism. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [PMID:18250452, PMID:22442494, PMID:24648522, PMID:33567255]\nsynonym: \"disruption of host canonical NF-kappaB cascade\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"disruption of host I-kappaB kinase/NF-kappaB cascade\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"negative regulation by symbiont of host I-kappaB kinase/NF-kappaB cascade\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"suppression by symbiont of host I-kappaB kinase/NF-kappaB cascade\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"symbiont-mediated suppression of host canonical NF-kappaB cascade\" RELATED []\nxref: VZ:695\nis_a: GO:0085032 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host NF-kappaB cascade\nintersection_of: GO:0044003 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host process\nintersection_of: negatively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0007249 ! canonical NF-kappaB signal transduction\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/25571\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/25581\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26686\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: jl\ncreation_date: 2010-07-27T03:32:44Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0085044\nname: symbiont-mediated disruption of host cuticle\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The process in which an organism effects a change that impairs the structure or function of the host organism cuticle. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [GOC:jl, GOC:pamgo_curators]\nsynonym: \"catabolism of host cuticle\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"degradation of host cuticle\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"disassembly by symbiont of host cuticle\" RELATED []\nis_a: GO:0052111 ! symbiont-mediated disruption of host anatomical structure\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/24127\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: jl\ncreation_date: 2010-07-27T01:08:15Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0098672\nname: symbiont-mediated suppression of host CRISPR-cas system\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process by which a symbiont inhibits or disrupts the CRISPR-cas system of its host. Bacteria and archaea use CRISPR-Cas adaptive immune systems to defend themselves from infection by bacteriophages (phages), and phages have various mechanisms to counter the CRISPR-cas system.\" [PMID:23242138, PMID:23446421, PMID:26416740, PMID:28749735]\nsynonym: \"anti-CRISPR\" BROAD []\nsynonym: \"CRISPR-cas system evasion by virus\" EXACT [VZ:3962]\nsynonym: \"evasion by virus of CRISPR-cas system\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"inhibition of host CRISPR-cas system by virus\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"suppression of host CRISPR-cas system\" EXACT []\nxref: VZ:3962\nis_a: GO:0052031 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host defense response\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/16423\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/18028\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29797\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: dos\ncreation_date: 2017-01-16T13:38:27Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0098673\nname: symbiont-mediated suppression of host DNA replication\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"Any process by which a virus inhibits DNA replication in its host cell. Some bacteriophages are known to do this, possibly as a way of increasing the pool of nucleotides available for virus replication.\" [PMID:17010157, PMID:21205014]\nsynonym: \"inhibition of host DNA replication by virus\" NARROW []\nxref: VZ:3948\nintersection_of: GO:0044003 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host process\nintersection_of: negatively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0006261 ! DNA-templated DNA replication\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28791\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: dos\ncreation_date: 2017-01-17T15:58:15Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0098676\nname: symbiont-mediated modulation of host virulence\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process by which a virus improves the virulence of its host for that host's respective host. Common in but not limited to bacteriophages; also occurs in phage-bearing bacteria infecting plants or animals for example. Mechanisms include the expression of factors that modulate a bacterial adhesion to a host cell, spread through host tissues, production of exotoxins or provide protection against host immune defenses.\" [PMID:10913072, PMID:11553559, PMID:22919604, PMID:8658163, VZ:3965]\nsynonym: \"modulation of host virulence by virus\" NARROW []\nxref: VZ:3965 \"Modulation of host virulence by virus\"\nis_a: GO:0044003 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host process\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/23326\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28791\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: dos\ncreation_date: 2017-01-19T11:59:46Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0098864\nname: symbiont-mediated stabilization of host tight cell-cell junction\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The process in which a symbiont organism that stabilizes the its host tight cell-cell junctions, making them less dynamic. The tight junction is a cell-cell junction that seals cells together in an epithelium in a way that prevents even small molecules from leaking from one side of the sheet to the other, and plays a role in the inflammatory response of the host.\" [PMID:25838979]\nsynonym: \"modification by symbiont of host tight cell-cell junction\" BROAD []\nsynonym: \"stabilization of host tight cell-cell junction\" BROAD []\nis_a: GO:0098865 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host tight cell-cell junction\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/25514\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0098865\nname: symbiont-mediated perturbation of host tight cell-cell junction\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The process in which an organism effects a change that impairs the structure or temporarily subverts the tight cell-cell junctions between cells of the host. Tight cell-cell junctions, a cell-cell junction that seals cells together in an epithelium in a way that prevents even small molecules from leaking from one side of the sheet to the other.\" [PMID:24287273]\nsynonym: \"disruption by symbiont of host tight cell-cell junction\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"disruption of host tight cell-cell junction\" BROAD []\nsynonym: \"modification by symbiont of host bicellular tight junctions\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"symbiont-mediated disruption of host tight cell-cell junction\" RELATED []\nis_a: GO:0044067 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host cell-cell junction\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/24127\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/25170\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/25514\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0098932\nname: symbiont entry into host cell via disruption of host cell wall peptidoglycan\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The disruption by a symbiont of host cell wall peptidoglycans to allow entry into the host cell.\" [GOC:dos, VZ:3940]\nsynonym: \"catabolism of host cell wall peptidoglycan by virus\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"degradation of host cell wall peptidoglycan by virus\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"degradation of host peptidoglycans during virus entry\" EXACT [VZ:3940]\nsynonym: \"disassembly by virus of host cell wall peptidoglycan\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"disruption by virus of host cell wall peptidoglycan during virus entry\" EXACT []\nxref: VZ:3940\nis_a: GO:0052009 ! symbiont-mediated disruption of host cell wall\nrelationship: part_of GO:0046718 ! symbiont entry into host cell\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26670\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0098933\nname: symbiont-mediated disruption of host cell envelope\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The process in which a symbiont effects a change that impairs the structure or function of the host cell envelope. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [ISBN:0198547684]\nsynonym: \"disruption by symbiont of host cell envelope\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0052008 ! symbiont-mediated disruption of host cellular anatomical structure\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0098994\nname: symbiont entry into host cell via disruption of host cell envelope\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The disruption by a symbiont of host cell envelope components to allow entry into the host cell.\" [GOC:dos]\nsynonym: \"disruption of host cell envelope during viral entry\" EXACT []\nxref: VZ:3938\nis_a: GO:0098933 ! symbiont-mediated disruption of host cell envelope\nrelationship: part_of GO:0046718 ! symbiont entry into host cell\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26670\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0098995\nname: symbiont entry into host cell via disruption of host cell envelope lipopolysaccharide\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The disruption by a symbiont of host cell wall lipopolysaccharides to allow entry into the host cell. For example a phage entering a Gram-negative bacterium may actively break down outer membrane lipopolysaccharides.\" [GOC:dos, VZ:3940]\nsynonym: \"degradation of host cell envelope lipopolysaccharide during viral entry\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"degradation of host lipopolysaccharide during virus entry\" EXACT [VZ:3940]\nsynonym: \"disassembly by virus of outer membrane lipopolysaccharide during viral entry\" NARROW []\nsynonym: \"disruption by virus of host envelope lipopolysaccharide during virus entry\" EXACT []\nxref: VZ:3939\nis_a: GO:0052009 ! symbiont-mediated disruption of host cell wall\nrelationship: part_of GO:0046718 ! symbiont entry into host cell\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26670\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0098996\nname: symbiont entry into host cell via disruption of host cell glycocalyx\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The disruption by a symbiont of host cell capsule to allow entry into the host cell.\" [GOC:dos]\nsynonym: \"catabolism of host glycocalyx during viral entry\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"degradation of host capsule during virus entry\" EXACT [VZ:3896]\nsynonym: \"degradation of host glycocalyx during viral entry\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"disassembly of glycocalyx during viral entry\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"disruption of host cell glycocalyx during viral entry\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"symbiont entry into host cell by disruption of host cell capsule\" EXACT []\nxref: VZ:3938\nis_a: GO:0098933 ! symbiont-mediated disruption of host cell envelope\nrelationship: part_of GO:0046718 ! symbiont entry into host cell\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26670\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0099016\nname: symbiont-mediated evasion of DNA end degradation by host\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process by which a symbiont evades and ends degradation of its DNA when free DNA ends are exposed. DNA ends are exposed during the life cycle of some viruses and these are targeted by host cells to destroy the virus. For example, some bacteriophages encode proteins that bind to free viral DNA ends, protecting them from degradation by host exonucleases.\" [GOC:dos, PMID:11894948, PMID:16949369, VZ:3963]\nsynonym: \"DNA end degradation evasion by virus\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"evasion by virus of DNA end degradation\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"evasion of DNA end degradation by host\" EXACT []\nxref: VZ:3963\nis_a: GO:0141177 ! symbiont-mediated evasion of recognition by host innate immune effector\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/23043\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26686\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/27250\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0099018\nname: symbiont-mediated evasion of host restriction-modification system\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process by which a symbiont evades the DNA restriction modification system of its host. This process occurs in phages to protein themselves from bacterial restriction enzyme systems. Some viruses encode their own methyltransferase in order to protect their genome from host restriction enzymes. Others directly inhibit restriction enzymes while some use unusual bases in their genome to avoid restriction.\" [PMID:20348932, PMID:23979432, PMID:24123737, VZ:3966]\nsynonym: \"evasion by virus of host restriction-modification system\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"evasion of host restriction-modification system\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"restriction-modification system evasion by virus\" EXACT []\nxref: VZ:3966\nis_a: GO:0141177 ! symbiont-mediated evasion of recognition by host innate immune effector\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/23043\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26686\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/27250\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0106259\nname: symbiont-mediated cell-to-cell migration in host\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The directional movement of a symbiont from one host cell to another.\" [GOC:vw, PMID:18456802, PMID:19262673, PMID:19816653, PMID:29567712]\nsynonym: \"cell-to-cell migration in host\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"symbiont-mediated dissemination across host cells\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0044001 ! migration in host\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/27786\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: hjd\ncreation_date: 2020-05-01T14:09:35Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0140133\nname: obsolete symbiont-mediated suppression of host cytokine production\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. A process by which a symbiont inhibits or disrupts cytokine production in the host organism. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [PMID:23083102]\ncomment: This term was obsoleted because it represents a readout.\nsynonym: \"negative regulation by symbiont of host cytokine production\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"suppression by symbiont of host cytokine production\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"suppression by symbiont of host cytokine secretion\" RELATED []\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/14553\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/29259\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\nconsider: GO:0052027\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2017-11-14T07:07:04Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0140267\nname: symbiont entry into host cell via permeabilization of host membrane\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The entry of a symbiont into the cytoplasm of a host cell, triggered by an interaction between the bilayer of a host membrane and a membrane-penetration symbiont protein. This process mediates the entry of some non-enveloped virus into host cells, and results in the release of the virus contents into the host cell cytoplasm.\" [PMID:20427561, PMID:25055856, VZ:985]\nsynonym: \"viral entry via permeabilization of host membrane\" NARROW []\nxref: VZ:985 \"Viral penetration via permeabilization of host membrane\"\nis_a: GO:0141171 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host membrane\nrelationship: part_of GO:0046718 ! symbiont entry into host cell\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26670\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2018-09-25T14:33:03Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0140321\nname: symbiont-mediated suppression of host autophagy\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which a symbiont inhibits or disrupts the normal execution of autophagy in the host cell. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [GOC:pg]\nsynonym: \"negative regulation by symbiont of host autophagy\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"suppression of host autophagy\" EXACT []\nintersection_of: GO:0044003 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host process\nintersection_of: negatively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0006914 ! autophagy\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/17055\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2019-04-03T09:21:48Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0140402\nname: symbiont-mediated disassembly of host stress granules\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"The process in which an organism effects a change that impairs the structure or function of the stress granule of the host organism. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction. Stress granules are dynamic cytoplasmic condensates formed through liquid-liquid phase separation. They act as a critical hub for both cellular stress adaptation and defense against viruses.\" [PMID:32353859, PMID:39345463]\nis_a: GO:0052008 ! symbiont-mediated disruption of host cellular anatomical structure\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31751\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2026-04-07T12:22:21Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0140411\nname: symbiont-mediated suppression of host stress granule assembly\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which a symbiont inhibits or disrupts the normal assembly of stress granule of the host organism. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction. Stress granules are dynamic cytoplasmic condensates formed through liquid-liquid phase separation. They act as a critical hub for both cellular stress adaptation and defense against viruses.\" [PMID:32353859, PMID:39345463]\nsynonym: \"symbiont-mediated inhibition of host stress granule assembly\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"symbiont-mediated inhibition of host stress granule formation\" EXACT []\nintersection_of: GO:0044003 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host process\nintersection_of: negatively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:0034063 ! stress granule assembly\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31751\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2026-04-07T12:38:51Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0140415\nname: effector-mediated perturbation of host defenses by symbiont\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process mediated by a molecule secreted by a symbiont that results in the modulation (either activation or suppression) of a defense response. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [PMID:30610168]\nsynonym: \"effector-mediated modulation of host defenses by symbiont\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0052200 ! symbiont-mediated response to host defenses\nintersection_of: GO:0140418 ! effector-mediated perturbation of host process by symbiont\nintersection_of: regulates_in_another_organism GO:0140546 ! defense response to symbiont\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28790\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2020-01-20T16:46:41Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0140418\nname: effector-mediated perturbation of host process by symbiont\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process mediated by a molecule secreted by a symbiont that results in the modulation (either activation or suppression) of a host structure or process. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [PMID:21467214]\nsynonym: \"