 of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [PMID:27473656, PMID:31375544]\nsynonym: \"inhibition by organism of defense-related host active oxygen species production\" EXACT []\nis_a: GO:0052031 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host defense response\nintersection_of: GO:0044003 ! symbiont-mediated perturbation of host process\nintersection_of: negatively_regulates_in_another_organism GO:1903409 ! reactive oxygen species biosynthetic process\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/25714\" xsd:anyURI\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2023-07-12T14:21:06Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0141088\nname: obsolete symbiont-mediated activation of host autophagy\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. A process in which a symbiont initiates, promotes, or enhances the activation of autophagy in the host cell. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [GOC:pg]\ncomment: This term was obsoleted because it represents the same process as symbiont-mediated activation of host autophagy ; GO:0039520.\nsynonym: \"induction of host autophagy\" EXACT []\nsynonym: \"positive regulation by symbiont of host autophagy\" EXACT []\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/17055\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/28790\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\nreplaced_by: GO:0039520\ncreated_by: pg\ncreation_date: 2023-07-19T14:39:06Z\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0141104\nname: symbiont-mediated activation of host G protein-coupled receptor signal transduction\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"A process in which a symbiont initiates, promotes, or enhances a G protein-coupled receptor signal transduction pathway in the host organism. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [PMID:15963708, PMID:18978047, PMID:25332123]\nis_a: GO:0052028 ! symbio