st cell cycle.\" [PMID:10946289, PMID:19308257]\ncomment: This term was obsoleted because it is an unnecessary grouping class.\nsynonym: \"cell cycle arrest in host\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"negative regulation by symbiont of host cell cycle\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"suppression of host cell cycle progression\" EXACT []\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/25571\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26692\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\nconsider: GO:0044071\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0044074\nname: obsolete negative regulation by symbiont of host translation\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. The process in which a symbiont organism stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of translation, the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of a protein, in its host organism.\" [MITRE:tk]\ncomment: This term was obsoleted because it represents the same process as symbiont-mediated suppression of host translation ; GO:0039604.\nsynonym: \"negative regulation of host translation by symbiont\" EXACT []\nproperty_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/26747\" xsd:anyURI\nis_obsolete: true\nreplaced_by: GO:0039604\n\n[Term]\nid: GO:0044081\nname: obsolete symbiont-mediated suppression of host nitric oxide-mediated signaling\nnamespace: biological_process\ndef: \"OBSOLETE. A process in which a virus interferes with, inhibits or disrupts a nitric oxide mediated signal transduction in its host organism. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.\" [MITRE:tk, PMID:23167250, PMID:29089430]\ncomment: This term was obsoleted because there is no evidence that this process exists; ie that a symbiont directly interferes with a host's notric oxide-mediated signaling pathway.\nsynonym: \"disruption of host nitric oxide-mediated signaling\" EXACT []\nsynonym: